WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.330 --> 00:00:02.220
It is pretty commonly understood that the

00:00:02.220 --> 00:00:04.218
biggest battery drain in most mobile phones

00:00:04.218 --> 00:00:08.470
is the display screen. You can tell this easily from the Android battery display

00:00:08.470 --> 00:00:10.960
even. But what hardware component do you

00:00:10.960 --> 00:00:13.190
think is the second biggest battery consumer

00:00:13.190 --> 00:00:16.160
on most mobile devices, the CPU, the

00:00:16.160 --> 00:00:20.670
cell WiFi radio antenna, memory, or the GPS?

